      <bioghist id="aspace_222ada841590cefc7ec5215244b1a9c3">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>Joseph's Brethren was an informal group composed of members of Yale's English literature faculty. Its membership included Charles Seymour (Y 1908 and former president of Yale), Chauncey B. Tinker (Y 1899), Henry S. Canby (SSS 1899), Lee W. Dodd (SSS 1899), Alfred R. Bellinger (Y 1917), and John C. Adams (Y 1896).</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_86a34d55a21b72837fe5e503a26c2d79">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The records consist of poetry and letters produced by members of Joseph's Brethren. Also included is an etched print of members' signatures by Emerson Tuttle (the first master of Davenport College).</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <arrangement id="aspace_d2c903f73a7ff0cb236c5785ba1e53f4">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>The records are arranged by type of material.</p>  
